original: Engloo, Tor, tf. länsarkitekt, Göteborg, f. 3il/5/06 i Sthlm. — Stud:ex. v. norra real i Sthlm 24, avg:ex. fr. KTH 28, fr. KKH 33. An&t. å privat arkitektkont. 28-32, egen arkit :verks. i Sthlm 33-45, arkit. i byggn’:styr. fr. 36, tf. länsarkit. i Gbg ,sed. 45. Led. av Sv. tekn:fören.
translated: Engloo, Tor, acting county architect, Gothenburg, born May 31, 1906 in Stockholm. He graduated from Norra Real high school in Stockholm in 1924, completed his engineering studies at KTH in 1928, and then studied at the Royal Academy of Fine Arts in Stockholm from 1928-1933. In the same year, he started working at a private architect's office until 1932, and then established his own architecture firm in Stockholm from 1933-1945. He was an architect in building control from 1936, and became the acting county architect in Gothenburg in 1945. He was a member of the Swedish Technical Association. Note: "m. partner's name" means he got married in the year 19xx.
